>>57340491
No, I’ve never experienced schizophrenia. Part of the reason why I think that those two abilities would be hard to write is that I feel like people underestimate them. For example: I don’t see how you could have an omnipotent villain that loses. The moment that they are aware of the hero, the villain can simply alter reality so that the hero never existed. In the case of omniscience, I once read an interesting thought experiment in a book, that demonstrates how in certain situations omniscience is actually a weakness. The experiment is that say you were omniscient, and playing a game of chicken where 2 aircraft fly directly towards each other and either one pilot swerves away and loses, or the planes collide and both players die. If your opponent knows that you are omniscient, and you don’t want to die then they can beat you 100% of the time. If your opponent knows that you know what they’ll do then they can simply choose to never swerve, and you will have to swerve out of the way every single time.
